  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1KI 5:1" />And <char style="w" strong="H2438">Hiram</char> <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> of <char style="w" strong="H6865">Tyre</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> his <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char>; for he had <char style="w" strong="H8085">heard</char> that they had <char style="w" strong="H4886">anointed</char> him <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> in the room of his <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>: for <char style="w" strong="H2438">Hiram</char> was <char style="w" strong="H3117">ever</char> a <char style="w" strong="H0157">lover</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.1 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">Hiram: also called, Huram</char></note> <verse eid="1KI 5:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="1KI 5:2" />And <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> to <char style="w" strong="H2438">Hiram</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, <verse eid="1KI 5:2" /><verse number="3" style="v" sid="1KI 5:3" />Thou <char style="w" strong="H3045">knowest</char> how that <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> my <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char> <char style="w" strong="H3201">could</char> not <char style="w" strong="H1129">build</char> an <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H8034">name</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> his <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">for</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4421">wars</char> which were about him on every <char style="w" strong="H5437">side</char>, until the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H5414">put</char> them under the <char style="w" strong="H3709">soles</char> of his <char style="w" strong="H7272">feet</char>. <verse eid="1KI 5:3" /><verse number="4" style="v" sid="1KI 5:4" />But now the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> my <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> hath given me <char style="w" strong="H5117">rest</char> on every <char style="w" strong="H5439">side</char>, <char style="add">so that there is</char> neither <char style="w" strong="H7854">adversary</char> nor <char style="w" strong="H7451">evil</char> <char style="w" strong="H6294">occurrent</char>. <verse eid="1KI 5:4" /><verse number="5" style="v" sid="1KI 5:5" />And, behold, I <char style="w" strong="H0559">purpose</char> to <char style="w" strong="H1129">build</char> an <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H8034">name</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> my <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char>, as the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> <char style="w" strong="H1696">spake</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> my <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, Thy <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char>, whom I will <char style="w" strong="H5414">set</char> upon thy <char style="w" strong="H3678">throne</char> in thy room, he shall <char style="w" strong="H1129">build</char> an <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> unto my <char style="w" strong="H8034">name</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.5 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">purpose: Heb. say</char></note> <verse eid="1KI 5:5" /><verse number="6" style="v" sid="1KI 5:6" />Now therefore <char style="w" strong="H6680">command</char> thou that they <char style="w" strong="H3772">hew</char> me cedar <char style="w" strong="H0730">trees</char> out of <char style="w" strong="H3844">Lebanon</char>; and my <char style="w" strong="H5650">se