  <para style="p">
    <verse number="7" style="v" sid="1KI 5:7" />¶ And it came to pass, when <char style="w" strong="H2438">Hiram</char> <char style="w" strong="H8085">heard</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1697">words</char> of <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char>, that he <char style="w" strong="H8055">rejoiced</char> <char style="w" strong="H3966">greatly</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char>, <char style="w" strong="H1288">Blessed</char> <char style="add">be</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>, which hath <char style="w" strong="H5414">given</char> unto <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> a <char style="w" strong="H2450">wise</char> <char style="w" strong="H1121">son</char> over this <char style="w" strong="H7227">great</char> <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>. <verse eid="1KI 5:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1KI 5:8" />And <char style="w" strong="H2438">Hiram</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> to <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char>, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, I have <char style="w" strong="H8085">considered</char> the things which thou <char style="w" strong="H7971">sentest</char> to me for: <char style="add">and</char> I will <char style="w" strong="H6213">do</char> all thy <char style="w" strong="H2656">desire</char> concerning <char style="w" strong="H6086">timber</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0730">cedar</char>, and concerning <char style="w" strong="H6086">timber</char> of <char style="w" strong="H1265">fir</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.8 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">considered: Heb. heard</char></note> <verse eid="1KI 5:8" /><verse number="9" style="v" sid="1KI 5:9" />My <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> shall bring <char style="add">them</char> <char style="w" strong="H3381">down</char> from <char style="w" strong="H3844"