    <verse number="13" style="v" sid="1KI 5:13" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char> <char style="w" strong="H5927">raised</char> a <char style="w" strong="H4522">levy</char> out of all <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char>; and the <char style="w" strong="H4522">levy</char> was <char style="w" strong="H7970">thirty</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H0376">men</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">5.13 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">levy: Heb. tribute of men</char></note> <verse eid="1KI 5:13" /><verse number="14" style="v" sid="1KI 5:14" />And he <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> them to <char style="w" strong="H3844">Lebanon</char>, <char style="w" strong="H6235">ten</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> a <char style="w" strong="H2320">month</char> by <char style="w" strong="H2487">courses</char>: a <char style="w" strong="H2320">month</char> they were in <char style="w" strong="H3844">Lebanon</char>, <char style="add">and</char> <char style="w" strong="H8147">two</char> <char style="w" strong="H2320">months</char> at <char style="w" strong="H1004">home</char>: and <char style="w" strong="H0141">Adoniram</char> <char style="add">was</char> over the <char style="w" strong="H4522">levy</char>. <verse eid="1KI 5:14" /><verse number="15" style="v" sid="1KI 5:15" />And <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char> had threescore and <char style="w" strong="H7657">ten</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> that <char style="w" strong="H5375">bare</char> <char style="w" strong="H5449">burdens</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H8084">fourscore</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H2672">hewers</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H2022">mountains</char>; <verse eid="1KI 5:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="1KI 5:16" />Beside the <char styl