    <verse number="62" style="v" sid="1KI 8:62" />¶ And the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, and all <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> with him, <char style="w" strong="H2076">offered</char> <char style="w" strong="H2077">sacrifice</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">before</char> the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>. <verse eid="1KI 8:62" /><verse number="63" style="v" sid="1KI 8:63" />And <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char> <char style="w" strong="H2076">offered</char> a <char style="w" strong="H2077">sacrifice</char> of peace <char style="w" strong="H8002">offerings</char>, which he <char style="w" strong="H2076">offered</char> unto the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>, <char style="w" strong="H8147">two</char> and <char style="w" strong="H6242">twenty</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H1241">oxen</char>, and an <char style="w" strong="H3967">hundred</char> and <char style="w" strong="H6242">twenty</char> <char style="w" strong="H0505">thousand</char> <char style="w" strong="H6629">sheep</char>. So the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> and all the <char style="w" strong="H1121">children</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> <char style="w" strong="H2596">dedicated</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char>. <verse eid="1KI 8:63" /><verse number="64" style="v" sid="1KI 8:64" />The same <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> did the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H6942">hallow</char> the <char style="w" strong="H8432">middle</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H2691">court</char> that <char style="add">was</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">before</char> the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char> of the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></