d="1KI 8:65" /><verse number="66" style="v" sid="1KI 8:66" />On the <char style="w" strong="H8066">eighth</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> he <char style="w" strong="H7971">sent</char> the <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> <char style="w" strong="H7971">away</char>: and they <char style="w" strong="H1288">blessed</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H3212">went</char> unto their <char style="w" strong="H0168">tents</char> <char style="w" strong="H8056">joyful</char> and <char style="w" strong="H2896">glad</char> of <char style="w" strong="H3820">heart</char> for all the <char style="w" strong="H2896">goodness</char> that the <char style="nd"><char style="w" strong="H3068">LORD</char></char> had <char style="w" strong="H6213">done</char> for <char style="w" strong="H1732">David</char> his <char style="w" strong="H5650">servant</char>, and for <char style="w" strong="H3478">Israel</char> his <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">8.66 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">blessed: or, thanked</char></note><verse eid="1KI 8:66" /></para>
