    <verse number="6" style="v" sid="1KI 12:6" />¶ And <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H7346">Rehoboam</char> <char style="w" strong="H3289">consulted</char> with the old <char style="w" strong="H2205">men</char>, that <char style="w" strong="H5975">stood</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">before</char> <char style="w" strong="H8010">Solomon</char> his <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char> while he yet <char style="w" strong="H2416">lived</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char>, How do ye <char style="w" strong="H3289">advise</char> that I <char style="w" strong="H7725">may</char> <char style="w" strong="H1697">answer</char> this <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char>? <verse eid="1KI 12:6" /><verse number="7" style="v" sid="1KI 12:7" />And they <char style="w" strong="H1696">spake</char> unto him, <char style="w" strong="H0559">saying</char>, If thou wilt be a <char style="w" strong="H5650">servant</char> unto this <char style="w" strong="H5971">people</char> this <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>, and wilt <char style="w" strong="H5647">serve</char> them, and <char style="w" strong="H6030">answer</char> them, and <char style="w" strong="H1696">speak</char> <char style="w" strong="H2896">good</char> <char style="w" strong="H1697">words</char> to them, then they will be thy <char style="w" strong="H5650">servants</char> for <char style="w" strong="H3117">ever</char>. <verse eid="1KI 12:7" /><verse number="8" style="v" sid="1KI 12:8" />But he <char style="w" strong="H5800">forsook</char> the <char style="w" strong="H6098">counsel</char> of the old <char style="w" strong="H2205">men</char>, which they had <char style="w" strong="H3289">given</char> him, and <char style="w" strong="H3289">consulted</char> with the young <char style="w" strong="H3206">men</char> that were grown <char style="w" strong="H1431">up</char> with him, <char style="add">and</char> which <char style="w" strong="H5975">stoo