  <para style="p">
    <verse number="11" style="v" sid="1KI 13:11" />¶ Now there <char style="w" strong="H3427">dwelt</char> <char style="w" strong="H0259">an</char> <char style="w" strong="H2205">old</char> <char style="w" strong="H5030">prophet</char> in <char style="w" strong="H1008">Beth-el</char>; and his <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> and <char style="w" strong="H5608">told</char> him all the <char style="w" strong="H4639">works</char> that the <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> had <char style="w" strong="H6213">done</char> that <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> in <char style="w" strong="H1008">Beth-el</char>: the <char style="w" strong="H1697">words</char> which he had <char style="w" strong="H1696">spoken</char> unto the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, them they <char style="w" strong="H5608">told</char> also to their <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char>. <verse eid="1KI 13:11" /><verse number="12" style="v" sid="1KI 13:12" />And their <char style="w" strong="H0001">father</char> <char style="w" strong="H1696">said</char> unto them, What <char style="w" strong="H1870">way</char> <char style="w" strong="H1980">went</char> he? For his <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char> had <char style="w" strong="H7200">seen</char> <char style="w" strong="H0335">what</char> <char style="w" strong="H1870">way</char> the <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> of <char style="w" strong="H0430">God</char> <char style="w" strong="H1980">went</char>, which <char style="w" strong="H0935">came</char> from <char style="w" strong="H3063">Judah</char>. <verse eid="1KI 13:12" /><verse number="13" style="v" sid="1KI 13:13" />And he <char style="w" strong="H0559">said</char> unto his <char style="w" strong="H1121">sons</char>, <char style="w" strong="H2280">Saddle</char> me the <char style="w" strong="H2543">ass</char>. So they <char style="w" strong="H2280">sadd